    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Calculates the standard deviation of the elements in the input vector. The underlying algorithm is used:</para><para><preformatted>
    Result = sqrt((sumOfSquares - sum<superscript>2</superscript> / blockSize) / (blockSize - 1))</preformatted></para><para><preformatted>    sumOfSquares = pSrc[0] * pSrc[0] + pSrc[1] * pSrc[1] + ... + pSrc[blockSize-1] * pSrc[blockSize-1]
    sum = pSrc[0] + pSrc[1] + pSrc[2] + ... + pSrc[blockSize-1]
</preformatted></para><para>There are separate functions for floating point, Q31, and Q15 data types. </para>    </detaileddescription>
